, or outside developers, to work on their special needs.  </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Many open source projects are dependent on other open source projects.  Working on one can give you valuable skills and understanding that can be a gateway to other projects.   </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Finally, you can build relationships with other developers and learn of other opportunities.  </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Working in a professional team','','inherit','closed','closed','','149-revision-v1','','','2024-02-10 23:35:55','2024-02-10 23:35:55','',149,'https://michaelkentburns.com/?p=161',0,'revision','',0),(162,1,'2024-02-10 23:36:34','2024-02-10 23:36:34','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Because of the rapid pace of technology development and market requirements, most web and application development is done by integrated teams.  No one person can do it all themselves. It takes a team of specialists working individually and cross discipline to be successful. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Some of the roles that are needed are:</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Project lead</strong> - responsible for planning how the individuals in the team can work together to complete the project.   This is usually done in cooperation with the whole team to come to consensus on next steps and how to keep the project moving.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Design lead</strong> - responsible for the technical design and requirements for each major piece of the solution.   This person is responsible for making sure that the contribution of all the team members will fit together and produce a good product.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Database designer</strong> - much of the interface between the different parts of the solution are stored in a database.   This person designs the specific tables, columns, and indexes needed to ensure proper communication and integrity.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Lead coder</strong> - this coder is the lead and will establish and enforce coding standards and facilitate code reviews.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Coder</strong> - an individual contributor that writes one or more specific code components. They may be front end, back end, or full stack coders depending on the languages they are proficient in. They will also design and write functional tests that ensure proper operation. These tests are often referred to as <strong>unit tests</strong> because they test the function of a specific code module.    </li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Tester</strong> - a person responsible for designing an implementing test suites that ensure that the individual code components operate together.   This person will often work with the individual coders to ensure their unit tests are properly written.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Documenter</strong> - works with the individual team members to understand how their contributions work and writes functional internal documentation and/or end user documentation.  The documentation may be in the form of a user manual but will also likely have on screen components such as roll-over tool tips or info links like ⓘ.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Source controller</strong> - ensures that all of the artifacts of the team members are properly kept in a repository and that all changes to those artifacts are also captured in the repository.  </li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Software_engineering\">Software engineering</a> team processes</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Requirements_analysis\">Requirements analysis</a></strong></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Scope and effort estimation</strong> </li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Prioritizing next steps and coordinating cadence and milestones</strong> - eg. <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Agile_software_development\">Agile</a> </li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Code_review\">Code reviews</a></strong></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Integration_testing\">Integration testing</a></strong></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Continuous_integration\">Continuous integration</a></strong></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Software_deployment\">Software deployment</a></strong> - </li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Programming_tool\">Team tools</a></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The team processes are often facilitated by specialized software.  Here is a list of some of those.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Repository_(version_control)\"><strong>Project repository manager</strong></a> - eg. GitHub</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Code_reviewing_software\"><strong>Code review software</strong></a> - eg. <a href=\"https://www.gerritcodereview.com/index.html\">Gerrit</a></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Bug, feature, and project management system</strong> - eg. <a href=\"https://www.atlassian.com/software/jira\">Jira</a></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_unit_testing_frameworks\"><strong>Unit testing framework</strong></a> - eg. </li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Source, build, testing and deployment automation system</strong> - eg. <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jenkins_(software)\">Jenkins</a></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Continuous_integration\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"><strong>Continuous integration system</strong></a> - eg. GitHub Actions</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Deployment framework</strong> - eg. <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kubernetes\">Kubernetes</a></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Build your brand</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The best way to build your skills as a team player and move up to more responsible positions is to find a role that you can already fill and join a team.   With a little effort you will be able to learn more about the other team members and their roles as well as learn more about the larger project.   As you develop your skills you can build a reputation of trust.   Open source software projects are a great opportunity because they depend on volunteer contributions.  But, it should be noted that all work done for open software projects is not done for free.  The companies or organizations that rely on open source software often have specific needs that are not necessarily shared by the community at large.   These organizations will often pay their employees, or outside developers, to work on their special needs.  </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Many open source projects are dependent on other open source projects.  Working on one can give you valuable skills and understanding that can be a gateway to other projects.   </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Finally, you can build relationships with other developers and learn of other opportunities.  </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Working in a team','','inherit','closed','closed','','149-revision-v1','','','2024-02-10 23:36:34','2024-02-10 23:36:34','',149,'https://michaelkentburns.com/?p=162',0,'revision','',0),(164,1,'2024-02-10 23:38:34','2024-02-10 23:38:34','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">GitHub</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>With the advent of <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Open-source_software\"><strong>open-source software</strong></a> there arose the need to have world wide access to the source code for the many projects.   <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Git\"><strong>Git</strong></a> is the source control tool invented for Linux development.  </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There are command line versions of git for all major desktop systems.  One of the more popular graphical interfaces for git is <a href=\"https://desktop.github.com\"><strong>GitDesktop</strong></a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/GitHub\"><strong>GitHub</strong></a> is a web interface for software development which uses Git for the source control features, and describes itself as collaborative version control.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>GitHub</strong> supports the creation of personal accounts.  Each account can contain a number of repositories, which can be made public or private access.   A personal account allows a developer to create a repository for each project that is being worked on.   On the developer\'s personal machine, a matching copy of the GitHub repository can be made in a process called cloning.   As work progresses on the local machine and certain testable milestones are reached, the local changes can be committed and pushed to the GitHub repository.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To get an idea of how this looks visit <a href=\"https://github.com/MichaelKentBurns\">my GitHub account.</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Using a GitHub account with repositories for each project that you have done allows others (if your repo is public) to see not only your code and documentation, but also the process you used to make the changes.   Each time you fix a bug or add a new feature, you should push that to GitHub with a comment that describes the fix or new feature.  </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Capture your learning in a repository.</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There are many tutorial sites to help you learn new skills.  As an example look at <strong><a href=\"https://www.frontendmentor.io\">Frontend Mentor.</a></strong>  This site is helpfully setup to capture your work for each challenge in a GitHub repository.  While it seems natural to download the starting material and jump right into the work, resist this urge and be very intentional in utilizing the features of Git.    </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When you begin a challenge, you should </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Create a new repository to house it.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Download the initial codebase provided, and push that to GitHub as your starting point.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Take the first step in the challenge, then test it, and finally push that work.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Test all the features you have done so far during the challenge.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>If you find a bug or perhaps a new feature or enhancement, stop and create an issue in the repository.   You don\'t have to fix it immediately, but it is very important to record the issue and steps to reproduce it.  </li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Continue your work stepwise capturing each step by pushing it with a descriptive comment.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Finally, or during the course of your work, look at the outstanding issues and pick one or two to address.  As each is fixed push the fix and close the issue. </li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When you are all finished with the challenge, take the time to create a ReadMe file in the repository.   In the first paragraph, and prominently marked, describe the specific skills demonstrated.  For instance if you are learning new HTML5 multimedia tags, list those.   This will be important when you start looking for work.  </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Finally, update your resumé, CV, or Upwork profile to have a link to that repository.  A prospect client reading your profile will be able to click on that and see a clear demonstration that you actually do know that specific skill.    One final note is that when you do a real project of your own design,  replace the link to the challenge repository with a link to your own original project repository.   Putting your skills to work on a project of your own design shows that you really know how and why to use that skill.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Create a project with other developers.</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As you learn with your friends take the opportunity to propose an original project that you all can work on together.   Get a consensus of the scope and focus of the project, but feel free to include some features that require a skill that only a few collaborators know well.   This teaches the real world reality that open-source software is a collaboration of many people to build and enhance projects that no single person can achieve alone. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Search GitHub for a project that you are interested in learning more about it. </h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Take some time to browse the galaxy of open-source projects in GitHub and find ones that you know about, or are interested in learning about.   You can actively follow the work of others, and can review the code that has been pushed to see how it has been coded.    Clone the repository to your local machine so you have a working copy.  As you test it out and find bugs or desired features, consider creating an issue in the GitHub project.   Note that some repositories have restrictions about who can do what.   By following projects, you will learn.  As you submit features, and if you get a chance to fix an issue you will start building your public credentials.   When you do that, be sure to update your resumé or CV or profile to point the projects you have participated in.   </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Work globally','','inherit','closed','closed','','59-revision-v1','','','2024-02-10 23:38:34','2024-02-10 23:38:34','',59,'https://michaelkentburns.com/?p=164',0,'revision','',0),(167,1,'2024-02-10 23:44:05','2024-02-10 23:44:05','<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"right\",\"id\":86,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignright size-large\"><img src=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/AdobeStock_142610858-1024x684.jpeg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-86\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Software development freelancing...</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There are many locations around the globe that are hotspots for software development.   If you happen to live in one of those places, jobs can come looking for you.   But there are many places around the world that have little or no jobs in this field.  In those places you need some extra skills to get and keep work, but it can be done.  This site is a place to find help and to build community of fellow developers.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Welcome</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>My intention with this main page is to tell a story of a journey that you might be on.  I\'ll try to keep it pretty brief and include \"Learn more...\" links so you can dive deeper as you need.   Hopefully you will find yourself on this journey and find where you are in the story.  When you do, I invite you to contact me.  My intention is that I can help guide you along.   I hope that this will become a community of like minded people.  I invite you to help me understand your needs and together we will keep you moving.  No tricks or fees are involved.   See my <a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/about-michael/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"22\">About page</a> for that background.  If you have questions or comments along the way please <a href=\"mailto: MichaelKentBurns@gmail.com\">email me</a>.   This site is a work in progress and I intend to develop it to meet the needs of my readers. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Developing your skills</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>While traditional full time employment brings a degree of long term job security, freelancers need to keep their current skills fresh in order to stay relevant.  High tech work is constantly changing with new fields opening up almost daily.  Those new fields often have a higher demand for skilled individuals.  Being willing and able to add new skills will increase your chances to find work and will often pay much better.  </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Front end web</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The World Wide Web is a rapidly evolving place, and it is a challenging field to stay fresh in.   Sometimes there are dramatic shifts in interactive tech.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/front-end-web/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"49\">Learn more...</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Back end web</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Back end technologies don\'t change as fast as front end, but...</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/back-end-web/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"52\">Learn more...</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Full stack</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>On the surface full stack development is just front end and back end, but there is more to consider...</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/full-stack/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"55\">Learn more...</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Working globally</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>With the advent of <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Open-source_software\"><strong>open-source software</strong></a> there arose the need to have world wide access to the source code for the many projects.   <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Git\"><strong>Git</strong></a> is the source control tool invented for Linux development.  <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/GitHub\"><strong>GitHub</strong></a> is a web interface for software development which uses Git for the source control features, and describes itself as collaborative version control.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>GitHub</strong> supports the creation of personal accounts.  Each account can contain a number of repositories, which can be made public or private access.   A personal account allows a developer to create a repository for each project that is being worked on.   On the developer\'s personal machine, a matching copy of the GitHub repository can be made in a process called cloning.   As work progresses on the local machine and certain testable milestones are reached, the local changes can be committed and pushed to the GitHub repository.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To get an idea of how this looks visit <a href=\"https://github.com/MichaelKentBurns\">my GitHub account.</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Using a GitHub account with repositories for each project that you have done allows others (if your repo is public) to see not only your code and documentation, but also the process you used to make the changes.   Each time you fix a bug or add a new feature, you should push that to GitHub with a comment that describes the fix or new feature.  </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/?page_id=59\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"59\">Learn more...</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Building your brand</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/building-your-brand/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"76\">Learn more...</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Finding work</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There are a number of <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Freelancer\">freelance</a> marketplaces online.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://www.upwork.com/freelance-jobs/\">Upwork</a> is one we recommend.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/finding-work/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"79\">Learn more...</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Latest Posts</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:latest-posts {\"align\":\"center\"} /-->','Home','','inherit','closed','closed','','2-revision-v1','','','2024-02-10 23:44:05','2024-02-10 23:44:05','',2,'https://michaelkentburns.com/?p=167',0,'revision','',0),(169,1,'2024-02-15 17:50:39','2024-02-15 17:50:39','','Michael at work','','inherit','open','closed','','michaelatwork','','','2024-02-15 17:51:21','2024-02-15 17:51:21','',0,'https://michaelkentburns.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/MichaelAtWork.jpeg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(171,1,'2024-02-15 17:54:43','2024-02-15 17:54:43','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Michael lives near Cedar Park, Texas with his wife Mary.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:group {\"layout\":{\"type\":\"flex\",\"flexWrap\":\"nowrap\"}} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><!-- wp:image {\"id\":39,\"width\":\"326px\",\"height\":\"244px\",\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img src=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/IMG_1613-1024x768.jpeg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-39\" style=\"width:326px;height:244px\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:group {\"layout\":{\"type\":\"constrained\"}} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><!-- wp:image {\"id\":169,\"width\":\"324px\",\"height\":\"auto\",\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img src=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/MichaelAtWork-1024x768.jpeg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-169\" style=\"width:324px;height:auto\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image --></div>\n<!-- /wp:group --></div>\n<!-- /wp:group -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Michael is a 40 year veteran software engineer.  The last 33 years was as a principal systems developer at <a href=\"http://sas.com\">SAS Institute</a>.  His main responsibility was the enterprise metadata server that connects all SAS products. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>He is now happily retired, but not yet done with the field.  This site is home base for his new focus of mentoring programmers in the art of software engineering.   The main emphasis is individuals living in a places that do not have software development jobs.  This means that their best opportunity is to go freelance.   Doing so allows them to stay in their culture and home community.   </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>...</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:social-links -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-social-links\"><!-- wp:social-link {\"url\":\"https://github.com/MichaelKentBurns\",\"service\":\"github\"} /-->\n\n<!-- wp:social-link {\"url\":\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/michaelkentburns/?lipi=urn%3Ali%3Apage%3Ad_flagship3_feed%3B6Dj3E8auRSy51Ad%2BgA7N%2FQ%3D%3D\",\"service\":\"linkedin\"} /-->\n\n<!-- wp:social-link {\"url\":\"MichaelKentBurns@gmail.com\",\"service\":\"mail\"} /-->\n\n<!-- wp:social-link {\"url\":\"https://www.facebook.com/michael.burns.906\",\"service\":\"facebook\"} /--></ul>\n<!-- /wp:social-links -->\n\n<!-- wp:social-links -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-social-links\"></ul>\n<!-- /wp:social-links -->','About Michael','','inherit','closed','closed','','22-revision-v1','','','2024-02-15 17:54:43','2024-02-15 17:54:43','',22,'https://michaelkentburns.com/?p=171',0,'revision','',0),(173,1,'2024-02-15 17:57:59','2024-02-15 17:57:59','<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"right\",\"id\":169,\"width\":\"431px\",\"height\":\"auto\",\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\",\"className\":\"is-style-default\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignright size-large is-resized is-style-default\"><img src=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/MichaelAtWork-1024x768.jpeg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-169\" style=\"width:431px;height:auto\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Software development freelancing...</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There are many locations around the globe that are hotspots for software development.   If you happen to live in one of those places, jobs can come looking for you.   But there are many places around the world that have little or no jobs in this field.  In those places you need some extra skills to get and keep work, but it can be done.  This site is a place to find help and to build community of fellow developers.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Welcome</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>My intention with this main page is to tell a story of a journey that you might be on.  I\'ll try to keep it pretty brief and include \"Learn more...\" links so you can dive deeper as you need.   Hopefully you will find yourself on this journey and find where you are in the story.  When you do, I invite you to contact me.  My intention is that I can help guide you along.   I hope that this will become a community of like minded people.  I invite you to help me understand your needs and together we will keep you moving.  No tricks or fees are involved.   See my <a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/about-michael/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"22\">About page</a> for that background.  If you have questions or comments along the way please <a href=\"mailto: MichaelKentBurns@gmail.com\">email me</a>.   This site is a work in progress and I intend to develop it to meet the needs of my readers. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Developing your skills</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>While traditional full time employment brings a degree of long term job security, freelancers need to keep their current skills fresh in order to stay relevant.  High tech work is constantly changing with new fields opening up almost daily.  Those new fields often have a higher demand for skilled individuals.  Being willing and able to add new skills will increase your chances to find work and will often pay much better.  </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Front end web</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The World Wide Web is a rapidly evolving place, and it is a challenging field to stay fresh in.   Sometimes there are dramatic shifts in interactive tech.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/front-end-web/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"49\">Learn more...</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Back end web</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Back end technologies don\'t change as fast as front end, but...</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/back-end-web/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"52\">Learn more...</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Full stack</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>On the surface full stack development is just front end and back end, but there is more to consider...</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/full-stack/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"55\">Learn more...</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Working globally</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>With the advent of <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Open-source_software\"><strong>open-source software</strong></a> there arose the need to have world wide access to the source code for the many projects.   <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Git\"><strong>Git</strong></a> is the source control tool invented for Linux development.  <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/GitHub\"><strong>GitHub</strong></a> is a web interface for software development which uses Git for the source control features, and describes itself as collaborative version control.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>GitHub</strong> supports the creation of personal accounts.  Each account can contain a number of repositories, which can be made public or private access.   A personal account allows a developer to create a repository for each project that is being worked on.   On the developer\'s personal machine, a matching copy of the GitHub repository can be made in a process called cloning.   As work progresses on the local machine and certain testable milestones are reached, the local changes can be committed and pushed to the GitHub repository.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To get an idea of how this looks visit <a href=\"https://github.com/MichaelKentBurns\">my GitHub account.</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Using a GitHub account with repositories for each project that you have done allows others (if your repo is public) to see not only your code and documentation, but also the process you used to make the changes.   Each time you fix a bug or add a new feature, you should push that to GitHub with a comment that describes the fix or new feature.  </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/?page_id=59\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"59\">Learn more...</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Building your brand</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/building-your-brand/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"76\">Learn more...</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Finding work</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There are a number of <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Freelancer\">freelance</a> marketplaces online.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://www.upwork.com/freelance-jobs/\">Upwork</a> is one we recommend.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/finding-work/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"79\">Learn more...</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Latest Posts</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:latest-posts {\"align\":\"center\"} /-->','Home','','inherit','closed','closed','','2-revision-v1','','','2024-02-15 17:57:59','2024-02-15 17:57:59','',2,'https://michaelkentburns.com/?p=173',0,'revision','',0),(174,1,'2024-02-15 17:58:55','2024-02-15 17:58:55','<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"right\",\"id\":169,\"width\":\"678px\",\"height\":\"auto\",\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\",\"className\":\"is-style-default\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignright size-large is-resized is-style-default\"><img src=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/MichaelAtWork-1024x768.jpeg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-169\" style=\"width:678px;height:auto\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Software development freelancing...</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There are many locations around the globe that are hotspots for software development.   If you happen to live in one of those places, jobs can come looking for you.   But there are many places around the world that have little or no jobs in this field.  In those places you need some extra skills to get and keep work, but it can be done.  This site is a place to find help and to build community of fellow developers.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Welcome</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>My intention with this main page is to tell a story of a journey that you might be on.  I\'ll try to keep it pretty brief and include \"Learn more...\" links so you can dive deeper as you need.   Hopefully you will find yourself on this journey and find where you are in the story.  When you do, I invite you to contact me.  My intention is that I can help guide you along.   I hope that this will become a community of like minded people.  I invite you to help me understand your needs and together we will keep you moving.  No tricks or fees are involved.   See my <a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/about-michael/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"22\">About page</a> for that background.  If you have questions or comments along the way please <a href=\"mailto: MichaelKentBurns@gmail.com\">email me</a>.   This site is a work in progress and I intend to develop it to meet the needs of my readers. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Developing your skills</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>While traditional full time employment brings a degree of long term job security, freelancers need to keep their current skills fresh in order to stay relevant.  High tech work is constantly changing with new fields opening up almost daily.  Those new fields often have a higher demand for skilled individuals.  Being willing and able to add new skills will increase your chances to find work and will often pay much better.  </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Front end web</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The World Wide Web is a rapidly evolving place, and it is a challenging field to stay fresh in.   Sometimes there are dramatic shifts in interactive tech.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/front-end-web/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"49\">Learn more...</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Back end web</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Back end technologies don\'t change as fast as front end, but...</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/back-end-web/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"52\">Learn more...</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Full stack</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>On the surface full stack development is just front end and back end, but there is more to consider...</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/full-stack/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"55\">Learn more...</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Working globally</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>With the advent of <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Open-source_software\"><strong>open-source software</strong></a> there arose the need to have world wide access to the source code for the many projects.   <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Git\"><strong>Git</strong></a> is the source control tool invented for Linux development.  <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/GitHub\"><strong>GitHub</strong></a> is a web interface for software development which uses Git for the source control features, and describes itself as collaborative version control.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>GitHub</strong> supports the creation of personal accounts.  Each account can contain a number of repositories, which can be made public or private access.   A personal account allows a developer to create a repository for each project that is being worked on.   On the developer\'s personal machine, a matching copy of the GitHub repository can be made in a process called cloning.   As work progresses on the local machine and certain testable milestones are reached, the local changes can be committed and pushed to the GitHub repository.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To get an idea of how this looks visit <a href=\"https://github.com/MichaelKentBurns\">my GitHub account.</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Using a GitHub account with repositories for each project that you have done allows others (if your repo is public) to see not only your code and documentation, but also the process you used to make the changes.   Each time you fix a bug or add a new feature, you should push that to GitHub with a comment that describes the fix or new feature.  </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/?page_id=59\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"59\">Learn more...</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Building your brand</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/building-your-brand/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"76\">Learn more...</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Finding work</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There are a number of <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Freelancer\">freelance</a> marketplaces online.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://www.upwork.com/freelance-jobs/\">Upwork</a> is one we recommend.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/finding-work/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"79\">Learn more...</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Latest Posts</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:latest-posts {\"align\":\"center\"} /-->','Home','','inherit','closed','closed','','2-revision-v1','','','2024-02-15 17:58:55','2024-02-15 17:58:55','',2,'https://michaelkentburns.com/?p=174',0,'revision','',0),(175,1,'2024-02-15 19:53:35','2024-02-15 19:53:35','<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Basic necessities in a development platform:</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Computer</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Internet access</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Web browser</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>File management - either GUI and/or command line commands.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Text editor</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Source management and distribution system</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Collaboration applications</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>While those are the basics, you will likely also need:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Web hosting service</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Interactive Development Environment (IDE)</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Remote development shell</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Common platforms:</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I\'ll not bother to describe all the many programs needed for each of these platforms since that will be found in the Development Tools page.   Rather, I\'ll discuss some of the unique attributes of each and how they relate.   You have probably already chosen a favorite platform, but may also be considering some alternatives.   </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Linux</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Almost all web hosting servers are running Linux so ultimately if you are going to do full stack development you will need to learn Linux.   Many developers have chosen to also use Linux as their local work computer.  We will discuss hosting servers a little later on this page, but for now we will consider Linux as a local development computer.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Linux of course can be installed on PC\'s and Macintoshes.   It can be installed in a virtual machine on either of those platforms.   It also can run native on Windows using <a href=\"https://cygwin.com\">Cygwin</a> which gives an existing Windows user the ability to use both Windows apps and Linux apps interchangeably.   That also eases the Linux learning curve.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>MacOS is based on Unix and the Mac Terminal app depends on Unix (Linux) shells for line mode interactive commands.   There are many different shells available to choose from, but the most commonly used one in my experience is BASH.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you choose to run Linux as your native OS then you will almost always use a graphical user interface.  </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Windows</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>With Windows you naturally have a graphical interface including Windows Explorer,  a web browser like InternetExplorer or Edge, an interactive command line tool like PowerShell or cmd.exe.   Using your browser there are applications galore that you can download and install.   </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In addition as mentioned above you can also install <a href=\"https://cygwin.com\">Cygwin</a> and get lots of Linux goodies as well.  </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Macintosh</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As mentioned above MacOS is really UNIX under the covers.   The Terminal window runs many different UNIX shells.   Many common development tools are available for download and install and ready for use.     </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>However, since Terminal gets you into the core of UNIX there are many UNIX, and Linux package managers available that will let you install just like you are in Linux.  Homebrew is one option.   Just Google \'<a href=\"https://duckduckgo.com/?hps=1&amp;q=package+managers+for+mac&amp;ia=web\">package managers for mac</a>\'</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Web hosting servers</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Most servers are virtual machines in a cloud server farms.   These are almost always headless meaning there is no display and keyboard.   You must access  these using some form of secure shell.   Checkout a google of \'<a href=\"https://duckduckgo.com/?q=ssh&amp;t=osx&amp;ia=web\">ssh</a>\'.   ssh and many programs that use it require secure certificates to be generated and installed on your local machine.  I will have a whole \'How to\' page dedicated to secure networking. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">How about you? </h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Give all of those options you probably already have a development platform of some sort and it\'s now time to talk about it.     I need to know about your setup, your needs, and your questions.    I have a \'<a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/challenge-tell-me-about-your-development-setup/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"184\">Tell me about your development setup</a>\' challenge page that you can use to tell me all about it.   So, go there and tell me.   </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Development platforms','','publish','closed','closed','','development-platforms','','','2024-03-13 16:46:57','2024-03-13 16:46:57','',0,'https://michaelkentburns.com/?page_id=175',0,'page','',0),(176,1,'2024-02-16 16:02:49','2024-02-15 19:53:35',' ','','','publish','closed','closed','','176','','','2024-02-16 16:02:49','2024-02-16 16:02:49','',0,'https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/2024/02/15/176/',10,'nav_menu_item','',0),(177,1,'2024-02-15 19:53:35','2024-02-15 19:53:35','<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Basic necessities in a development platform:</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Computer</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Internet access</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Web browser</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>File management - either GUI and/or command line commands.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Text editor</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Source management and distribution system</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Collaboration applications</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>While those are the basics, you will likely also need:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Web hosting service</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Interactive Development Environment (IDE)</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Remote development shell</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Common platforms:</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I\'ll not bother to describe all the many programs needed for each of these platforms since that will be found in the Development Tools page.   Rather, I\'ll discuss some of the unique attributes of each and how they relate.   You have probably already chosen a favorite platform, but may also be considering some alternatives.   </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Linux</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Almost all web hosting servers are running Linux so ultimately if you are going to do full stack development you will need to learn Linux.   Many developers have chosen to also use Linux as their local work computer.  We will discuss hosting servers a little later on this page, but for now we will consider Linux as a local development computer.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Linux of course can be installed on PC\'s and Macintoshes.   It can be installed in a virtual machine on either of those platforms.   It also can run native on Windows using <a href=\"https://cygwin.com\">Cygwin</a> which gives an existing Windows user the ability to use both Windows apps and Linux apps interchangeably.   That also eases the Linux learning curve.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>MacOS is based on Unix and the Mac Terminal app depends on Unix (Linux) shells for line mode interactive commands.   There are many different shells available to choose from, but the most commonly used one in my experience is BASH.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you choose to run Linux as your native OS then you will almost always a graphical user interface.  </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Windows</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>With Windows you naturally have a graphical interface include Windows Explorer,  a web browser like Edge, an interactive command line tool like PowerShell or cmd.exe.   Using your browser there are applications galore that you can download and install.   </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In addition as mentioned above you can also install <a href=\"https://cygwin.com\">Cygwin</a> and get lots of Linux goodies as well.  </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Macintosh</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As mentioned above MacOS is really UNIX under the covers.   The Terminal window runs many different UNIX shells.   Many common development tools are available for download and install and ready for use.     </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>However, since Terminal gets you into the core of UNIX there are many UNIX, and Linux package managers available that will let you install just like you are in Linux.  Homebrew is one option.   Just Google \'<a href=\"https://duckduckgo.com/?hps=1&amp;q=package+managers+for+mac&amp;ia=web\">package managers for mac</a>\'</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Web hosting servers</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Most servers are virtual machines in a cloud server farms.   These are almost always headless meaning there is no display and keyboard.   You must access  these using some form of secure shell.   Checkout a google of \'<a href=\"https://duckduckgo.com/?q=ssh&amp;t=osx&amp;ia=web\">ssh</a>\'.   ssh and many programs that use it require secure certificates to be generated and installed on your local machine.  I will have a whole \'How to\' page dedicated to secure networking. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">How about you? </h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Give all of those options you probably already have a development platform of some sort and it\'s now time to talk about it.     I need to know about your setup, your needs, and your questions.    I have a \'Your development setup\' challenge page that you can use to tell me all about it.   So, go there and tell me.   </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Development platforms','','inherit','closed','closed','','175-revision-v1','','','2024-02-15 19:53:35','2024-02-15 19:53:35','',175,'https://michaelkentburns.com/?p=177',0,'revision','',0),(178,1,'2024-02-15 20:03:10','2024-02-15 20:03:10','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Once you have read some of this site it is good to put some of that to a test with a challenge.    There are often several paths that will get you to one of these challenges.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When you complete a challenge tell me what you learned and what questions you still have.   For now, we can do that through email and later we can get more formal.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Please make sure that you report your experience.</strong>  To do this, create an email to <a href=\"mailto:MichaelKentBurns@gmail.com\">MichaelKentBurns@gmail.com</a>.  Start your email by copying the text of the challenge into your message.   Make the subject of your email the title of the challenge (from the top of the page).  Then as you follow the steps, simply insert your comments, questions, and problems encountered.   Complete the email with a summary of what you learned.    </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>So, dive in:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/challenge-tell-me-about-yourself-so-i-know-how-i-can-help-you/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"181\"><strong>Tell me about yourself </strong>so I know how I can help you.</a></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/challenge-tell-me-about-your-development-setup/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"184\"><strong>Tell me about your development setup</strong>,</a> what you already can do, and what you want to be able to do.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/challenge-setup-your-own-github-account-and-install-desktop-github-app/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"187\"><strong>Setup your own GitHub account</strong> and install Desktop GitHub app.</a></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/challenge-capture-a-tutorial-project-in-a-github-repository/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"222\"><strong>Take any development challenge </strong>and record your work in a GitHub repository.</a> </li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Lots more to come... </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Take a challenge','','publish','closed','closed','','take-a-challenge','','','2024-03-09 13:13:31','2024-03-09 13:13:31','',0,'https://michaelkentburns.com/?page_id=178',0,'page','',0),(179,1,'2024-02-16 16:02:49','2024-02-15 20:03:10',' ','','','publish','closed','closed','','179','','','2024-02-16 16:02:49','2024-02-16 16:02:49','',0,'https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/2024/02/15/179/',11,'nav_menu_item','',0),(180,1,'2024-02-15 20:03:10','2024-02-15 20:03:10','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Once you have read some of this site it is good to put some of that to a test with a challenge.    There are often several paths that will get you to one of these challenges.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When you complete a challenge tell me what you learned and what questions you still have.   For now, we can do that through email and later we can get more formal.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>So, dive in:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Tell me about yourself </strong>so I know how I can help you.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Tell me about your development setup</strong>, what you already can do, and what you want to be able to do.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Setup your own GitHub account and install Desktop GitHub app.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Take any development challenge and record your work in a GitHub repository. </li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Lots more to come... </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Take a challenge','','inherit','closed','closed','','178-revision-v1','','','2024-02-15 20:03:10','2024-02-15 20:03:10','',178,'https://michaelkentburns.com/?p=180',0,'revision','',0),(181,1,'2024-02-15 20:12:37','2024-02-15 20:12:37','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Please write an email to <a href=\"mailto:MichaelKentBurns@gmail.com\">MichaelKentBurns@gmail.com</a> (following the instructions on the <a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/take-a-challenge/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"178\">Challenges page</a>) and include these things:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Your name and email address, as well as any other contact info like Facebook, LinkedIn, Twitter,  Discord, GitHub or other profiles you might have. </li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Where you live and what your city or country is like.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Your education.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Your development training and experience.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Your career experience and goals. </li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>What your hobbies are.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>What kind of development you have already done.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>What you would like to learn to do.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There is another challenge for you to tell me about your current development setup.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Challenge: Tell me about yourself so I know how I can help you.','','publish','closed','closed','','challenge-tell-me-about-yourself-so-i-know-how-i-can-help-you','','','2024-03-09 13:15:42','2024-03-09 13:15:42','',0,'https://michaelkentburns.com/?page_id=181',0,'page','',0),(183,1,'2024-02-15 20:12:37','2024-02-15 20:12:37','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Please write an email to <a href=\"mailto:MichaelKentBurns@gmail.com\">MichaelKentBurns@gmail.com</a> and include these things:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Your name and email address, as well as any other contact info like Facebook, LinkedIn, Twitter,  Discord, GitHub or other profiles you might have. </li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Where you live and what your city or country is like.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Your education.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Your development training and experience.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Your career experience and goals. </li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>What your hobbies are.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>What kind of development you have already done.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>What you would like to learn to do.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There is another challenge for you to tell me about your current development setup.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Challenge: Tell me about yourself so I know how I can help you.','','inherit','closed','closed','','181-revision-v1','','','2024-02-15 20:12:37','2024-02-15 20:12:37','',181,'https://michaelkentburns.com/?p=183',0,'revision','',0),(184,1,'2024-02-15 20:25:58','2024-02-15 20:25:58','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You may wish to start by reading my <a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/development-platforms/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"175\">Development platforms</a> page then come back here and tell me about your current setup in an email to <a href=\"mailto:MichaelKentBurns@gmail.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">MichaelKentBurns@gmail.com</a> (following the instructions on the <a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/take-a-challenge/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"178\">Challenges page</a>).</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Tell me about: </strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Your computer model, memory, disk, processor.   </li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Additional screens you have attached.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Your internet access and how it works for you.   What you can and cannot do.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Your operating system and release.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>What browser(s) you use.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Do you use a command line tool/shell and which one?</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Do you use a simple text editor or a graphical editor or IDE?</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Do you use GitHub or other site to publish your work?</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Do you use command line git to commit and push work or do you use a program like GitHub Desktop or other graphical tools?</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Do you host your finished work so it is visible to the public? </li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>What do you like best about your current setup?</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>What don\'t you like, or what could be better? </li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Challenge: Tell me about your development setup.','','publish','closed','closed','','challenge-tell-me-about-your-development-setup','','','2024-03-09 13:16:50','2024-03-09 13:16:50','',0,'https://michaelkentburns.com/?page_id=184',0,'page','',0),(186,1,'2024-02-15 20:25:58','2024-02-15 20:25:58','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You may wish to start by reading my <a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/development-platforms/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"175\">Development platforms</a> page then come back here and tell me about your current setup in an email to <a href=\"mailto:MichaelKentBurns@gmail.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">MichaelKentBurns@gmail.com</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Tell me about: </strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Your computer model, memory, disk, processor.   </li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Additional screens you have attached.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Your internet access and how it works for you.   What you can and cannot do.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Your operating system and release.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>What browser(s) you use.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Do you use a command line tool/shell and which one?</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Do you use a simple text editor or a graphical editor or IDE?</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Do you use GitHub or other site to publish your work?</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Do you use command line git to commit and push work or do you use a program like GitHub Desktop or other graphical tools?</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Do you host your finished work so it is visible to the public? </li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>What do you like best about your current setup?</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>What don\'t you like, or what could be better? </li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Challenge: Tell me about your development setup.','','inherit','closed','closed','','184-revision-v1','','','2024-02-15 20:25:58','2024-02-15 20:25:58','',184,'https://michaelkentburns.com/?p=186',0,'revision','',0),(187,1,'2024-02-15 20:33:12','2024-02-15 20:33:12','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In my <a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/work-globally/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"59\">Work globally</a> page I discuss the importance of using GitHub to make yourself known and show off your talents.  It is also a great place to discover other projects that you can learn from and teams that you can participate in. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Don\'t forget to send me an email (following the instructions on the <a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/take-a-challenge/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"178\">Challenges page</a>) to <a href=\"mailto:MichaelKentBurns@gmail.com\">MichaelKentBurns@gmail.com</a>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Go to <a href=\"http://GitHub.com\">GitHub.com</a></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Read up on what it is and how it works.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Click the \'Sign up\' button and create yourself a free account. </li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Search around for projects that interest you and get a feel for how they are layed out.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Visit my page:  <a href=\"https://github.com/MichaelKentBurns\">https://github.com/MichaelKentBurns</a> and checkout some of my repositories.   One you might find interesting is <a href=\"https://github.com/MichaelKentBurns/MichaelKentBurns.com\">MichaelKentBurns.com</a> which is the project which is the repository for this site.   Yes, I keep an entire WordPress site captured in a repository.  </li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Also checkout the repository in which I captured the process I went through in developing my next challenge:  <a href=\"https://github.com/MichaelKentBurns/Challenge-Interactive-rating-component\">Challenge-Interactive-rating-component</a>, look at the text of the file Notes.md to see how I did it. </li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Note that the GitHub site is where the public facing copy of your repository is stored.  But, you don\'t want to do your work there, in fact you can\'t.  Instead the idea is that you create a copy of that repository locally on your own machine and develop in that copy.     There are two ways to upload your progress at each step on the way.  One is the original \'git\' cli command.   That requires a little learning which is not a bad idea.  But there is a companion Desktop app that looks a lot like the GitHub.com site.  It is called <a href=\"https://desktop.github.com/\">GitHub Desktop</a>.  You can download that from this link now and install it.  Alternatively, once you have created your first repository and want to \'clone\' it to your desktop machine, the cloning process will offer to install the desktop app for you and feed it the command to do the copy of your new repository.   </li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>To get a feel for how this works, take the time to create a \'my first repo\' repository and clone it to your desktop machine.   Then code a simple \'HelloWorld.html\' page.  If you are not familiar with \"<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/%22Hello,_World!%22_program\">Hello, World!</a>\" checkout the wikipedia page.  There you will find source for this simple starter app in almost any language known, including HTML.   When you have coded it, then use the desktop app to commit that and push it to your public repository.   </li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Once you have it working locally and have pushed it to the GitHub site you can actually create a \'GitHub Page\' to publish the working page for the whole world to see.   To do that when looking at the repository in GitHub.com, you will see a number of tabs along the top:  \'&lt;&gt; Code\', \'Issues\', ... \'Settings\'.   Pick the Settings.   It will automatically fill in the repository name, and the Default branch will probably be set to \'main\'.    On the left side of the screen in the sidebar, under \'Code and automation\' there is an item named \'Pages\'.  Pick that.   Once there it\'s pretty easy.  Under \'Source\' there is a selector to pick the branch.   That should already say \'Deploy from a branch\'.   Leave that as it is.  Below that is a section labeled \'Branch\'.  In there are two buttons that should say \'None\' and \'Save\'.  It is not real obvious but click the \'None\' button and select the \'main\' branch\'.  Finally press the \'Save\' button.   It should then tell you \'Your GitHub Pages site is currently being built from the&nbsp;<code>main</code>&nbsp;branch.&nbsp;<a href=\"https://docs.github.com/articles/configuring-a-publishing-source-for-github-pages/\">Learn more about configuring the publishing source for your site</a>.\'  In a few moments you can refresh that page and see a note near the top that says something like \'Your site is live at&nbsp;<a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.github.io/Hello-World/\">https://michaelkentburns.github.io/Hello-World/</a>Last&nbsp;<a href=\"https://github.com/MichaelKentBurns/Hello-World/actions/runs/7922504847\">deployed</a>&nbsp;by&nbsp;<img width=\"14\" height=\"14\" src=\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/5041124?s=28&amp;v=4\" alt=\"@MichaelKentBurns\"><a href=\"https://github.com/MichaelKentBurns\">MichaelKentBurns</a>&nbsp;1 minute ago\'.   Just click that link or the \'Visit site\' button. </li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Now that it is published live, you can make a small change to your local copy of the program and commit and push that to GitHub and within a short time your change will be live.   On the right side of the repository page, near the bottom you will see a section labeled \'Deployments\'.  </li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You have probably done this now!  Congratulations.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Don\'t forget to finish your email with a link to your new repository.  </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Challenge: Setup your own GitHub account and install Desktop GitHub app.','','publish','closed','closed','','challenge-setup-your-own-github-account-and-install-desktop-github-app','','','2024-03-09 13:19:47','2024-03-09 13:19:47','',0,'https://michaelkentburns.com/?page_id=187',0,'page','',0),(190,1,'2024-02-15 20:33:12','2024-02-15 20:33:12','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In my <a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/work-globally/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"59\">Work globally</a> page I discuss the importance of using GitHub to make yourself known and show off your talents.  It is also a great place to discover other projects that you can learn from and teams that you can participate in. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Challenge: Setup your own GitHub account and install Desktop GitHub app.','','inherit','closed','closed','','187-revision-v1','','','2024-02-15 20:33:12','2024-02-15 20:33:12','',187,'https://michaelkentburns.com/?p=190',0,'revision','',0),(192,1,'2024-02-15 20:48:52','2024-02-15 20:48:52','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In my <a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/work-globally/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"59\">Work globally</a> page I discuss the importance of using GitHub to make yourself known and show off your talents.  It is also a great place to discover other projects that you can learn from and teams that you can participate in. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Go to <a href=\"http://GitHub.com\">GitHub.com</a></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Read up on what it is and how it works.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Click the \'Sign up\' button and create yourself a free account. </li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Search around for projects that interest you and get a feel for how they are layed out.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Visit my page:  <a href=\"https://github.com/MichaelKentBurns\">https://github.com/MichaelKentBurns</a> and checkout some of my repositories.   One you might find interesting is <a href=\"https://github.com/MichaelKentBurns/MichaelKentBurns.com\">MichaelKentBurns.com</a> which is the project which is the repository for this site.   Yes, I keep an entire WordPress site captured in a repository.  </li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Also checkout the repository in which I captured the process I went through in developing my next challenge:  <a href=\"https://github.com/MichaelKentBurns/Challenge-Interactive-rating-component\">Chal